# Agent Workflow

## Lifecycle

`draft -> classified -> planned -> assigned -> queued -> running ->
awaiting_review -> approved -> applied -> closed`.

Terminals: `cancelled`, `failed`, `expired`, `blocked`, `superseded`.

## Rules

- Background workers never auto-commit and never auto-push.
- Workers produce artifacts and an evidence pack for review.
- Cursor remains the orchestrator for final edits and merge decisions.
- Every policy-relevant action emits an immutable audit event.
- Worker runs write `runs/<agent>/<run-id>/manifest.json` and `runs/status/*.json`.
- Worker dispatch supports `start`, `start-next`, `status`, `stop`, and `review`.

## Handoff

Inputs and outputs follow `schemas/handoff.schema.json`. Acceptance requires:

- no unresolved critical blockers
- verification checklist complete
- referenced file paths must exist
